"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Try to place heating block in sterile environemnt to avoid falling contamination, given that the tubes need to remain open during this step. It may take longer if you did not remove all excess ethanol in previous step. <\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#84CE84","section_duration":2700,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":973968,"guid":"4B51C3B537D04AC982FC376450EF17C9","previous_id":973967,"previous_guid":"A4759A7A30F2432DB7A9BE70D437161D","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"9CBB7A66BE074BA288189671DD8C026D","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"RNA pellet wash"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"3A6196852B684807876FCD96C4EED834","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Dissolve the RNA (or DNA) pellet in the appropriate amount of RNAse\/DNase-free water depending on expected yields and needed final concentration.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#84CE84","section_duration":2700,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":973969,"guid":"918B51F0BD3311EAA961976B4A2720A1","previous_id":973933,"previous_guid":"A4554C23E6214B83A24B1272DD97AB19","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"745D5926E87749F69EE3023A51ED5894","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"RNA extraction"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"154B5947AAE94EAFA83EB40141E5B798","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>With the sterile razor blade\/scalepel, cut two vertical lines down the filter, one cut on opposite sides of the cylindrical filter (<\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">i.e.,<\/span><span> make one vertical cut, then turn the filter 180 degrees and make another cut).<\/span><\/div><div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/public\/a441450d32d78f7ead3ec72e7aea29e31f08cc66367d9e373e40d6bebec3c290\/cdqn497w.png\" \/><\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"2997C8841839493AB6A622109A18A996","order_id":2,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/public\/a441450d32d78f7ead3ec72e7aea29e31f08cc66367d9e373e40d6bebec3c290\/cdqn497w.png\" \/><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":973970,"guid":"06377BF0BD3411EAA961976B4A2720A1","previous_id":973969,"previous_guid":"918B51F0BD3311EAA961976B4A2720A1","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"129C924217234909B688BB3AE8E1BFE0","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"RNA extraction"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"C98B5D59EEB14495856B0E272E7FE02D","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Cut around the top and bottom of the cylindrical filter.<\/div><div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/public\/a441450d32d78f7ead3ec72e7aea29e31f08cc66367d9e373e40d6bebec3c290\/cdqq497w.jpg\" \/><\/div><div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/public\/a441450d32d78f7ead3ec72e7aea29e31f08cc66367d9e373e40d6bebec3c290\/cdqs497w.jpg\" \/><\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"87F3E05AB5A44299B31BA58240D0CF1E","order_id":2,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/public\/a441450d32d78f7ead3ec72e7aea29e31f08cc66367d9e373e40d6bebec3c290\/cdqq497w.jpg\" \/><\/div>"}},{"id":1054726,"guid":"4A5B46B3091E47B98CFE05962F323DD9","order_id":3,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/public\/a441450d32d78f7ead3ec72e7aea29e31f08cc66367d9e373e40d6bebec3c290\/cdqs497w.jpg\" \/><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":973971,"guid":"452F2C90BD3411EAA961976B4A2720A1","previous_id":973970,"previous_guid":"06377BF0BD3411EAA961976B4A2720A1","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"CC4878D185D04E2FBD4CCCA7F136AF04","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"RNA extraction"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"E1AE0D7883264852AB4EA39AF3857FC6","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">This should allow you to peel the filter off in two pieces. Using sterile forceps, peel the filter<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">off the plastic and fold it up enough to fit nto the bead beating tube of choice (recommended tube: Zymo ZR BashingBead Lysis Tubes (S6012-50))<\/div><div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/public\/a441450d32d78f7ead3ec72e7aea29e31f08cc66367d9e373e40d6bebec3c290\/cdqu497w.jpg\" \/><\/div><div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/public\/a441450d32d78f7ead3ec72e7aea29e31f08cc66367d9e373e40d6bebec3c290\/cdqw497w.jpg\" \/><\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"E809710D95BF47B3AA5F451F12621ABB","order_id":2,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/public\/a441450d32d78f7ead3ec72e7aea29e31f08cc66367d9e373e40d6bebec3c290\/cdqu497w.jpg\" \/><\/div>"}},{"id":1054726,"guid":"BBDB6D76F76B40C7B184DAAE4DE47C58","order_id":3,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/public\/a441450d32d78f7ead3ec72e7aea29e31f08cc66367d9e373e40d6bebec3c290\/cdqw497w.jpg\" \/><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0}],"document":null,"materials":[],"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">This extraction protocol uses a modified filter extraction method and bead-beating technique. This verison uses a technique to attempt to increase the biomass recovered from low-biomass samples by cutting out the filter from the sterivex unit with a sterile razor blade or scalpel. The filter is then placed directly into the bead bashing lysis tube and is homogenized with the starting solution. The protocol has been tested and used on oligotrophic seawater samples that contain a low amount of biomass. <\/div><\/div>","changed_on":1594131434}